snippet: Navigating a war zone is no longer anything new for those remaining in Benghazi, more than four years after the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.

byline.contributor: David D. Kirkpatrick reported from Cairo, and Suliman Ali Zway from Tripoli, Libya.
byline.original: By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK and SULIMAN ALI ZWAY

abstract: Battle for control over Benghazi, Libya, could be most significant obstacle to resolution of many conflicts that have riven country; while 2012 attack on American mission in city is focus of politicians in United States, residents of city view attack as milestone in city's descent into chaos.
lead_paragraph: Navigating a war zone is no longer anything new for those remaining in Benghazi, more than four years after the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.

headline.print_headline: Key Hurdle to Libya Peace May Be Battle for Benghazi
headline.main: Benghazi Battle May Be Key Hurdle to Libya Peace
